I'm ready to help you explore the codebase and design implementation plans! 

Let me start by getting oriented with the project structure:

<bash>
find /Users/patrick/workingdir/personal-agent -type f -name "*.go" -o -name "*.ts" -o -name "*.tsx" | head -30
</bash>

<bash>
cat /Users/patrick/workingdir/personal-agent/README.md
</bash>

<bash>
ls -la /Users/patrick/workingdir/personal-agent/
</bash>

I can see this is a personal agent project with:
- A Go backend in `packages/go-backend/`
- A desktop UI in `packages/desktop/` (TypeScript/React)
- Recent work on providers, skills, and UI improvements

The git status shows several modified files related to:
- Agent components and UI
- Backend provider management (OpenAI, and a new Gemini provider)
- E2E tests

I'm ready to explore the codebase in detail and create implementation plans. What would you like me to help design?
